description: "EXPECTED: parses clean. Probes the renderer's v4 dot rule (2026-07-08): $obj has no label and no gloss, so being an undercut target no longer promotes it to the full diamond — it renders as a trivial anchor dot (isSubstantiveJunction), keeping only the gjunction--undercut tint, and shows no strength bar. $resp is undercut-shaped (concludes @target, opposite of $obj's ~@target, with $obj as premise), so its ONLY rendered edge is the undercut onto $obj — drawn railway-style (solid rail + cross-ties, v5) — and its dropped @target conclusion surfaces as the hover ghost. Focus-mode regression: selecting $resp must card/light $obj (its one linked member) while @objection-basis (widened keep, unlinked) dims; $resp's popup is replaced by its self-card."
